<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376694>
    dc:description "FIGURES 270–273. Phaeoxantha (Euphaeoxantha) bucephala W. Horn, two syntypes from Santiago del Estero, Argentina (SDEI). 270–271—habitus: 270—♂, 25.3 mm, LT; 271—♀, 23.3 mm, PLT; 272—original labels of the LT; 273—mandibles and labrum, ♂, LT. Bars = 1 mm. Image credit Kevin Weissing." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376694/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376696>
    dc:description "FIGURES 274–282. Phaeoxantha (Euphaeoxantha) bucephala W. Horn. 274–275—mandibles: 274—♂, “Brazil, Amazonas”; 275—♀, Bolivia, N. Camiri (COSJ); 276–277—labrum: 276—♂, “Paraguay, Rio Pilcomayo” (CCJM ex JWCW) 277—♀, Bo- livia, N. Camiri (COSJ); 278—protarsus, ♂, ibid (CCJM); 279—pronotum, ♂, Bolivia, N. Camiri (COSJ); 280—aedeagus, Rio Pilcomayo (CCJM); 281–282—elytron: 281—♂, Bolivia, N. Camiri (CCJM); 282—♀, ibid (COSJ). Bars= 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376696/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

